			<div class="blog-faq">
				<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>What exactly is included in a mommy makeover?</h3>
					<p>A mommy makeover is a customized combination of procedures that typically includes a tummy tuck, breast lift or augmentation, and liposuction. The exact procedures are tailored to each patient's individual needs and aesthetic goals. Some women may also choose to include additional treatments such as thigh lifts or arm lifts.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long after pregnancy should I wait before getting a mommy makeover?</h3>
					<p>Most surgeons recommend waiting at least six months after childbirth and completing breastfeeding before undergoing a mommy makeover. This allows your body to recover from pregnancy and ensures that your weight has stabilized. Waiting also gives you time to determine if the changes to your body are something you want to address surgically.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Is a mommy makeover safe?</h3>
					<p>When performed by a qualified and experienced board-certified plastic surgeon, a mommy makeover is generally safe. Like any surgery, it carries some risks, including infection, bleeding, scarring, and anesthesia-related complications. Choosing a reputable surgeon and following all pre- and post-operative instructions significantly reduces these risks.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How long is the recovery period after a mommy makeover?</h3>
					<p>Most patients need two to four weeks of recovery before returning to work and light activities. Full recovery typically takes six to eight weeks. During this time, you should avoid heavy lifting and strenuous exercise. Having a support system at home to help with childcare and household tasks is highly recommended.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Will I have visible scars after a mommy makeover?</h3>
					<p>All surgeries result in some scarring, but Dr. Johar takes great care to place incisions in discreet locations that can be easily hidden by underwear and swimwear. Over time, scars typically fade and become less noticeable. Following your surgeon's scar care instructions can further minimize their appearance.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Can I get pregnant after a mommy makeover?</h3>
					<p>Yes, you can get pregnant after a mommy makeover, but future pregnancies may undo the results of the surgery. For this reason, most surgeons recommend completing your family before undergoing these procedures. If you do become pregnant after a mommy makeover, a C-section may be recommended to preserve the surgical results.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How much does a mommy makeover cost in India?</h3>
					<p>The cost of a mommy makeover in India varies depending on the specific procedures performed and the surgeon's experience. Prices typically range from INR 1,50,000 to INR 5,00,000. During your consultation, you will receive a detailed cost estimate based on your personalized treatment plan. Many clinics also offer EMI options for added convenience.</p>
				</div>
